[background arg="res://Bg/art_room.png" fade="1.0"]
set {c3s2_reyes_tried} = false
set {c3s2_outsider_tried} = false
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/The art room is filled with half-finished canvases and clay-dusted tables..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
The art room is filled with half-finished canvases and clay-dusted tables.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Ms. Reyes the art teacher sorts through supplies with trembling hands..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
Ms. Reyes, the art teacher, sorts through supplies with trembling hands.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	join Celestine (half) left
	join "Ms Reyes" (half) right
	"Ms Reyes": This is devastating. Art Week was supposed to celebrate our students' creativity.
	"Ms Reyes": Now all anyone will remember is the destruction.
	Celestine: Ms. Reyes, I'm trying to find out who did this. Can you help me understand the situation?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Ms. Reyes sets down the brushes she was holding..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	"Ms Reyes" sets down the brushes she was holding.
	"Ms Reyes": I'll tell you what I know. Ask me anything.
	Celestine: Tell me about Mia's sculpture. Why was it the centerpiece?
	"Ms Reyes": Because it was extraordinary. Mia poured your heart into that piece.
	"Ms Reyes": She won the regional competition last month. The judges called it "emotionally transcendent."
	"Ms Reyes": For a high school student to create something so moving... it's rare.
	Celestine: Did anyone have a problem with Mia winning?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Ms. Reyes hesitates glancing toward the door..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	"Ms Reyes" hesitates, glancing toward the door.
	"Ms Reyes": Art is competitive. There's always... tension when one student excels.
	Celestine: Anyone specific?
	"Ms Reyes": Victor Lim. He's incredibly talented. Technically, he might even be better than Mia.
	"Ms Reyes": But your work lacks... soul. It's precise but cold.
	"Ms Reyes": He entered the same competition. Didn't even place.
	Celestine: How did he take it?
	"Ms Reyes": He didn't say much. But I've seen you staring at Mia's sculpture.
	"Ms Reyes": Not with admiration. With something darker.
	Celestine: Where can I find Victor?
	"Ms Reyes": He should be in the courtyard, setting up your display. He insisted on being part of Art Week despite... well.
	Celestine: Despite what?
	"Ms Reyes": His sculpture wasn't selected for the main exhibit. The committee felt it was technically impressive but lacked emotional resonance.
	"Ms Reyes": He took it personally.
	Celestine: Thank you, Ms. Reyes. This helps.
	leave "Ms Reyes"
	join Mark (Mark_half) right
	Mark: So we have a jealous rival who got rejected from the exhibit?
	Celestine: Motive and opportunity. But we need more than that.
	Celestine: Let's talk to Victor.
	leave Celestine
	leave Mark
else:
	join Conrad (half) left
	join "Ms Reyes" (half) right
	"Ms Reyes": This is devastating. Art Week was supposed to celebrate our students' creativity.
	"Ms Reyes": Now all anyone will remember is the destruction.
	Conrad: Ms. Reyes, I'm trying to find out who did this. Can you help me understand the situation?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Ms. Reyes sets down the brushes she was holding..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
