[background arg="res://Bg/courtyard.png" fade="1.0"]
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Victor stands near a small display at the edge of the courtyard arms crossed..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
Victor stands near a small display at the edge of the courtyard, arms crossed.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/His sculpture—a geometric abstract piece—sits ignored while crowds gather near the crime scene..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
His sculpture - a geometric abstract piece - sits ignored while crowds gather near the crime scene.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	join Celestine (half) left
	join Victor (half) right
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Victor's eyes narrow as Conrad approaches..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Victor's eyes narrow as Celestine approaches.
	Victor: Let me guess. You're here to accuse me.
	Celestine: I'm here to ask questions. Everyone is a potential witness.
	Victor: Witness? I wasn't anywhere near the courtyard last night.
	Celestine: I didn't mention when it happened.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Victor's jaw tightens..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Victor's jaw tightens.
	Victor: It's obvious. The sculpture was fine yesterday. Destroyed this morning. Basic logic.
	Celestine: You seem upset.
	Victor: Of course I'm upset. Everyone's making this about Mia. "Poor Mia, her beautiful sculpture."
	Victor: No one even looks at my work. No one ever does.
	Celestine: Your sculpture is technically impressive.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Victor scoffs..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Victor scoffs.
	Victor: "Technically impressive." That's what they always say. Right before they give the award to someone else.
	Victor: Do you know how many hours I practice? How many techniques I've mastered?
	Victor: And Mia just... feels her way through it. No discipline. No rigor.
	Victor: Yet everyone loves her work and ignores mine.
	Celestine: That sounds frustrating.
	Victor: Frustrating doesn't begin to cover it.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Victor uncrosses his arms stepping closer..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Victor uncrosses your arms, stepping closer.
	Victor: But I didn't destroy her sculpture. I'm not a criminal.
	Victor: Besides, I was home all night. Ask my parents.
	Celestine: We might do that.
	Victor: You do that.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Victor turns back to his ignored display..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Victor turns back to you ignored display.
	Victor: Now leave me alone. Some of us have actual art to show.
	leave Victor
	join Mark (Mark_half) right
	Mark: He's bitter. Really bitter.
	Celestine: Bitter enough to destroy Mia's sculpture?
	Mark: He says he was home, but that alibi needs verification.
	Celestine: Let's gather more evidence before we confront anyone.
	Mark: What are you thinking?
	Celestine: The paint-stained cloth. If we can match it to Victor's supplies...
	Celestine: And the note. The handwriting might tell us something.
	leave Celestine
	leave Mark
else:
	join Conrad (half) left
	join Victor (half) right
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Victor's eyes narrow as Conrad approaches..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
