[background arg="res://Bg/courtyard.png" fade="0.5"]
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Conrad returns to where he found Mia..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Celestine returns to where she found Mia.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/She's sitting on a bench staring at the spot where her sculpture once stood..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	She's sitting on a bench, staring at the spot where your sculpture once stood.
	join Celestine (half) left
	join Mia (half) right
	Celestine: Mia, can I ask you a few more questions?
	Mia: Of course. Anything to help find who did this.
	Celestine: Did you have any conflicts with other students? Anyone who might wish you harm?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Mia thinks carefully..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Mia thinks carefully.
	Mia: I try to get along with everyone. I don't... I don't understand competition.
	Mia: Art isn't about winning. It's about expressing what's inside you.
	Celestine: What about Victor Lim?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Mia's expression softens with sadness..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Mia's expression softens with sadness.
	Mia: Victor is talented. Really talented.
	Mia: But he's always so focused on being better than everyone else.
	Mia: He once told me I "got lucky" with my regional win. That the judges didn't understand "real" technique.
	Celestine: How did that make you feel?
	Mia: Sad. Not for me. For him.
	Mia: He works so hard, but he's working for the wrong reasons.
	Mia: Art should come from love, not from wanting to be superior.
	Celestine: Do you think Victor could have done this?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Mia hesitates..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Mia hesitates.
	Mia: I... I don't want to accuse anyone. But the note...
	Mia: "Not everyone deserves to shine." That sounds like something someone says when they feel overlooked.
	Mia: Victor always felt overlooked.
	Celestine: Thank you, Mia. I'm going to find the truth.
	join "Diwata Laya" (Half) leftmost
	[signal arg="laya_start"]
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Diwata Laya materializes beside Conrad her form shimmering faintly..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	"Diwata Laya" materializes beside Celestine, your form shimmering faintly.
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]Celestine. May I see the note?[/color][/i]
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Conrad passes it to her discreetly careful not to draw attention..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Celestine passes it to you discretely, careful not to draw attention.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Diwata Laya holds the paper gently closing her eyes..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	"Diwata Laya" holds the paper gently, closing your eyes.
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]I sense... pain. Deep, festering pain.[/color][/i]
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]The person who wrote this has been hurting for a long time.[/color][/i]
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]They didn't destroy that sculpture out of hate. They destroyed it out of desperation.[/color][/i]
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]They believed this was the only way anyone would see them.[/color][/i]
	"Celestine (Thinking)": That's tragic.
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]It is. But tragedy does not excuse the harm they caused.[/color][/i]
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]Find them, Celestine. Not to punish, but to understand.[/color][/i]
	[signal arg="laya_end"]
	leave "Diwata Laya"
	leave Mia
	join Mark (Mark_half) right
else:
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Conrad returns to where he found Mia..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Conrad returns to where he found Mia.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/She's sitting on a bench staring at the spot where her sculpture once stood..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	She's sitting on a bench, staring at the spot where your sculpture once stood.
