	Mia: Victor is talented. Really talented.
	Mia: But he's always so focused on being better than everyone else.
	Mia: He once told me I "got lucky" with my regional win. That the judges didn't understand "real" technique.
	Conrad: How did that make you feel?
	Mia: Sad. Not for me. For him.
	Mia: He works so hard, but he's working for the wrong reasons.
	Mia: Art should come from love, not from wanting to be superior.
	Conrad: Do you think Victor could have done this?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Mia hesitates..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Mia hesitates.
	Mia: I... I don't want to accuse anyone. But the note...
	Mia: "Not everyone deserves to shine." That sounds like something someone says when they feel overlooked.
