	Conrad: Thank you, Mia. I'm going to find the truth.
	join "Diwata Laya" (Half) leftmost
	[signal arg="laya_start"]
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Diwata Laya materializes beside Conrad her form shimmering faintly..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	"Diwata Laya" materializes beside Conrad, your form shimmering faintly.
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]Conrad. May I see the note?[/color][/i]
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Conrad passes it to her discreetly careful not to draw attention..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Conrad passes it to you discretely, careful not to draw attention.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s2/Diwata Laya holds the paper gently closing her eyes..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	"Diwata Laya" holds the paper gently, closing your eyes.
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]I sense... pain. Deep, festering pain.[/color][/i]
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]The person who wrote this has been hurting for a long time.[/color][/i]
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]They didn't destroy that sculpture out of hate. They destroyed it out of desperation.[/color][/i]
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]They believed this was the only way anyone would see them.[/color][/i]
	"Conrad (Thinking)": That's tragic.
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]It is. But tragedy does not excuse the harm they caused.[/color][/i]
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]Find them, Conrad. Not to punish, but to understand.[/color][/i]
	[signal arg="laya_end"]
	leave "Diwata Laya"
	leave Mia
	join Mark (Mark_half) right
label suspect_choice
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	Celestine: Based on what we've learned, who should we focus on?
	- Ms. Reyes might be covering for a student she favors. | [if {c3s2_reyes_tried} == false]
		set {c3s2_reyes_tried} = true
		[signal arg="wrong_choice"]
		set {chapter3_score} -= 5
		Celestine: No. Ms. Reyes was genuinely distressed about the damage.
		Celestine: She has no motive to destroy her own student's work. And she pointed us toward Victor herself.
		Celestine: If she wanted to protect him, she wouldn't have mentioned his resentment.
		jump suspect_choice
	- An outsider vandal who hates the school. | [if {c3s2_outsider_tried} == false]
		set {c3s2_outsider_tried} = true
		[signal arg="wrong_choice"]
		set {chapter3_score} -= 5
		Celestine: The note says "Not everyone deserves to shine." That's personal.
		Celestine: An outsider wouldn't care about who "deserves" recognition at our school.
		Celestine: This was done by someone who feels overlooked. Someone inside.
		jump suspect_choice
	- Victor. He has motive, knowledge, and the emotional connection to this crime.
		set {chapter3_score} += 10
		Celestine: Victor resents Mia's success. He was rejected from the exhibit.
		Celestine: He has access to the school and knows where the sculpture was displayed.
		Celestine: And the note reflects exactly what he's been expressing\: feeling invisible while Mia shines.
	Mark: So what do we do?
	Celestine: We need hard evidence. The paint cloth, the note's handwriting, anything that proves Victor was there.
	Celestine: Let's check the art room storage.
	leave Celestine
	leave Mark
else:
	Conrad: Based on what we've learned, who should we focus on?
	- Ms. Reyes might be covering for a student she favors. | [if {c3s2_reyes_tried} == false]
		set {c3s2_reyes_tried} = true
		[signal arg="wrong_choice"]
		set {chapter3_score} -= 5
		Conrad: No. Ms. Reyes was genuinely distressed about the damage.
		Conrad: She has no motive to destroy her own student's work. And she pointed us toward Victor herself.
		Conrad: If she wanted to protect him, she wouldn't have mentioned his resentment.
		jump suspect_choice
	- An outsider vandal who hates the school. | [if {c3s2_outsider_tried} == false]
		set {c3s2_outsider_tried} = true
		[signal arg="wrong_choice"]
		set {chapter3_score} -= 5
		Conrad: The note says "Not everyone deserves to shine." That's personal.
		Conrad: An outsider wouldn't care about who "deserves" recognition at our school.
		Conrad: This was done by someone who feels overlooked. Someone inside.
		jump suspect_choice
	- Victor. He has motive, knowledge, and the emotional connection to this crime.
		set {chapter3_score} += 10
		Conrad: Victor resents Mia's success. He was rejected from the exhibit.
		Conrad: He has access to the school and knows where the sculpture was displayed.
		Conrad: And the note reflects exactly what he's been expressing\: feeling invisible while Mia shines.
	Mark: So what do we do?
	Conrad: We need hard evidence. The paint cloth, the note's handwriting, anything that proves Victor was there.
	Conrad: Let's check the art room storage.
	leave Conrad
	leave Mark
jump c3s3/
